<div class="section" id="intro">
  <h2 class="first">A Hidim turns a torrent into a regular PNG image</h2>

  <p>You save the png yourself. You can post it anywhere. People can decode it, but it can't be searched for... it won't turn up in searches for those torrents, unless you provide text that matches.</p>

  <p>Follow us on twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/michaeln3">@michaeln3</a> and <a href="http://twitter.com/zootella">@zootella</a></p>
</div>

<div id="create_wrapper">
  <div id="create" class="section">
    <h2>Make a hidim</h2>
    <%= render :partial => 'form' -%>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="extension_wrapper">
  <div id="extension" class="section">
    <a class="screenshot-thumb" rel="lightbox" href="/firefox-extension/screenshot-1.png">
      <img src="/firefox-extension/screenshot-1.thumb.png"/>
    </a>
    <h2>Decode a hidim</h2>
    <p>
      Bookmarklet:
      <a class="bookmarklet" href="javascript:(function(){if(typeof%20HidimReader!='undefined'){HidimReader.init();}else{var%20n=document.createElement('script');n.setAttribute('language','JavaScript');n.setAttribute('src','http://hid.im/javascripts/hidim_reader.js');document.body.appendChild(n);}})();;">Decode Hidim</a> 
      <small>(requires Firefox 3 or Safari 4)</small>
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/12858/">
        <img class="icon" src="/images/firefox-16.png">
        Get the Firefox extension from addons.mozilla.org
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<% unless flash[:notice].blank? -%>
  <div id="notice">
    <% if Array === flash[:notice] -%>
      <%= flash[:notice].map{|line| "<p>#{line}</p>"} -%>
    <% else -%>
      <%= flash[:notice] -%>
    <% end -%>
  </div>
<% end -%>


<div class="section" id="recent">
  <h2>Sample hidim'd torrents</h2>
  <ul>
    <% @hidims.first(3).each do |hidim| -%>
      <li class="hidim-item">
	<%= render :partial => 'hidim', :object => hidim -%>
      </li>
    <% end -%>
  </ul>
</div>

<p>Read more about how hidims work:
  <%= link_to "The Bookmarklet", about_url(:action => 'bookmarklet') -%>,
  <%= link_to "Hidim Format", about_url(:action => 'format') -%>
</p>

